                <p>C++ is one of the most popular programming languages, especially in competitive programming. Currently, most young people prioritize learning C++ to build a foundation and programming mindset when first starting to explore programming. The basic C++ course is designed with the most basic and easy-to-understand knowledge to help you access it easily.</p>
                <h2 id="introduction">Course goal:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Helps you learn C++ from scratch quickly and easily.</li>
                    <li>Equips you with the necessary knowledge and skills to write simple C++ programs.</li>
                    <li>Helps you understand and use important concepts in C++.</li>
                    <li>Creates a foundation for you to self-study and develop more complex C++ programs.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 id="curriculum">Target audience:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>This course is for beginners who have absolutely no programming knowledge, or those who have lost the basics and want to regain basic programming knowledge, specifically C++.</li>
                </ul>
                <h2 id="rating">Teaching method:</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>The course combines theory and practice.</li>
                    <li>Students will learn through video lectures, theoretical readings, practice exercises, and theory tests.</li>
                    <li>Students will be able to ask and answer questions directly with their classmates and the course manager.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="learning-outcome">
                    <h2 id="certificate">What will you learn?</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>After completing the course, students will have enough knowledge and skills to write simple C++ programs.</li>
                        <li>Students will understand and use important concepts in C++ easily.</li>
                        <li>Students will have a solid foundation to self-study and develop more complex C++ programs.</li>
                        <li>The course will help students improve their logical thinking, problem-solving, and programming skills effectively.</li>
                    </ul>
